# Redis configuration

Optional Redis persistence for web deployments and Node-side caching.

## Environment variables

| Variable | Default | Description |
|----------|---------|-------------|
| `VOICEBOX_REDIS_ENABLED` | `false` | Enable Redis persistence |
| `VOICEBOX_REDIS_URL` | — | Full connection URL (`redis://` or `rediss://`) |
| `VOICEBOX_REDIS_HOST` | `127.0.0.1` | Redis host when URL is not set |
| `VOICEBOX_REDIS_PORT` | `6379` | Redis port |
| `VOICEBOX_REDIS_PASSWORD` | — | Optional password |
| `VOICEBOX_REDIS_DB` | `0` | Logical database index |
| `VOICEBOX_REDIS_KEY_PREFIX` | `voicebox:` | Key namespace prefix |
| `VOICEBOX_REDIS_CONNECT_TIMEOUT_MS` | `10000` | Connection timeout |
| `VOICEBOX_REDIS_MAX_RETRIES` | `3` | Max retries per request |
| `VOICEBOX_REDIS_RETRY_DELAY_MS` | `200` | Base retry delay |
| `VOICEBOX_REDIS_MAX_RETRY_DELAY_MS` | `5000` | Retry delay cap |
| `VOICEBOX_REDIS_OFFLINE_QUEUE` | `true` | Queue commands while reconnecting |
| `VOICEBOX_REDIS_LAZY_CONNECT` | `true` | Connect on first use |
| `VOICEBOX_LOG_LEVEL` | `debug` (dev) / `info` (prod) | Logging verbosity |

## Local development

```bash
# Start Redis locally (Docker)
docker run --name voicebox-redis -p 6379:6379 -d redis:7-alpine

# Enable in your shell or .env
export VOICEBOX_REDIS_ENABLED=true
export VOICEBOX_REDIS_HOST=127.0.0.1
export VOICEBOX_REDIS_PORT=6379
```

When Redis is disabled or unreachable at startup, the connection manager falls back to an in-memory cache so the application remains functional.

## Usage

```typescript
import { loadRedisConfig, RedisConnectionManager } from '@voicebox/redis';

const manager = new RedisConnectionManager(loadRedisConfig());
await manager.connect();

await manager.set('session:demo', JSON.stringify({ user: 'local' }), 3600);
const value = await manager.get('session:demo');

process.on('SIGINT', async () => {
  await manager.disconnect();
  process.exit(0);
});
```
